6. tnAHbwA They appointed together a time, 
								liloqitaAli 
								for fighting; and sometimes for other purposes. (K.)

Also, both words, (TA,) or the former only; (K, MF;) but 
							nisiIoCN↓ is quoted in this sense, from IAar, who is said to have pronounced it thus, erroneously, for nasiIoCN; (TA;) Wine; 


							(IAar;) drink that dispels the reason. (K.)

[It became produced; it originated; 
								Eano 
								from another thing. See 4.]

Hence, (S, M, TA,) AnqD AlHimolu Zahorahu (S, M, A, Msb, K *) The load made his back to sound by reason of its weight: (M:) or pressed heavily upon him, (S, M, Msb, K,) so that his back was heard to make a sound such as is termed 
								naqiyD; (M, K; * i. e. the sound of the camel's saddle when it becomes infirm by reason of the weight of the load; (Bd, xciv. 3;) or a slight sound, as when a man makes a smacking with his tongue (yunoqiDu) to his ass, in driving him: (TA:) or oppressed his back by its weight: (Msb:) or rendered him lean, or emaciated; 
								jaEalahu niqoDFA, i. e. mahozuwlFA. (Ibn- 'Arafeh, K.) Thus in the phrase AlRaciI OanoqaDa Zahoraka, (S, M, K,) in [xciv. 3, of] the Kur. (S, M.)

naAba UilaI AllReh; (K;) and 
							AnAb Uilayohi↓, (S, K,) inf. n. UinaAbapN; (TA:) obedience He returned from disobedience to obedience to God, he returned unto God [repenting]: he repented; (S, K:) or the latter, he returned unto God; syn. rajaEa (Msb:) or nAb signifies he kept to obedience unto God: [this is given in the K as another and distinct signification of nAb:] and AnAb signifies as before explained or he returned to the performance of God, command; not departing 
								from anything thereof: or be returned time after time: the In. signification, accord. to the Kesh-sháf and AHei, is he entered upon the good turn. (TA, where for Alxyl read Alxyr.)
